		  <div class="featurette" id="1">
				<h2 class="featurette-heading">Becoming a Member or Mentor of FIRST<sup>&reg;</sup> Team 1764</h2>
				<p class="lead">Are you interested in robotics? Do you have explicit knowledge of business, designing, engineering, website or graphic design? Would you like to gain knowledge in any of the above areas? You should consider becoming a member or mentor for Liberty Robotics FIRST<sup>&reg;</sup> Team 1764. We have a wide variety of areas for you to explore and can offer an infinite amount of knowledge from professionals trained in the field. For more information concerning membership or mentoring opportunities please contact Gary Pierson, head coach, at <a href="mailto:gpierson@liberty.k12.mo.us">gpierson@liberty.k12.mo.us</a>.</p>
		  </div>
		  <hr class="featurette-divider">
		  <div class="featurette featurette-right" id="2">
				<h2 class="featurette-heading">Mentoring</h2>
				<p class="lead">FIRST<sup>&reg;</sup> Team 1764 is very proud of their mentors and invite interested candidates to take the initiative to join us! We currently have have a ratio of nearly 1 mentor for every 5 students, which means that our mentors should never feel overwhelmed or burdened; in the rare event you do, then help is just a mentor away. Even as we boast a high number of mentors we promise that there will never be a dull moment- unless that is what you choose. We would like to caution highly motivated individuals; FIRST<sup>&reg;</sup> Team 1764 Robotics is extremely addictive!</p>
		  </div>
		  <hr class="featurette-divider">
			<div class="featurette" id="3">
				<h2 class="featurette-heading">Membership</h2>
				<p class="lead">Our team enjoys a great deal of diversity and encourages growth of every magnitude. We are very excited to announce that our team is maintaining a 4:1 male to female ratio - go girls! Our members work in all aspects of robotics, from graphic design to actually building the robot. Never fear for a lack of interesting subjects to work on; robotics has it all. Sound interesting? Email, Gary Pierson, head coach at <a href="mailto:gpierson@liberty.k12.mo.us">gpierson@liberty.k12.mo.us</a> or visit the <a href="../teamstructure">Team Structure</a> page to read about leadership opportunities available with FIRST<sup>&reg;</sup> Team 1764.</p>
		  </div>
		  <hr class="featurette-divider">
			<div class="featurette featurette-right" id="4">
				<h2 class="featurette-heading">Why Join?</h2>
				<p class="lead">FIRST<sup>&reg;</sup> Team 1764 provides a safe environment in which you are able to express yourself and grow intellectually. What could be better than driving a robot you helped to build within a time-span of six weeks? Even better, robotics maintains its team momentum throughout the year and offers a large variety of exciting activities. Join robotics, FIRST<sup>&reg;</sup> Team 1764 will have you quoting Dean Kamen and Woodie Flowers in no time!</p>
